Collections is a group of individual objects.

Collections is used to represent group of discrete objects as a single unit.

The Java Collection Framework is  both homogeneous and heterogeneous collections.
Collection framework is a set of interfaces , implementation classes and algorithms.

We can have dynamic length, so we don't need to declare the length like in the arrays.

We can perform operations on the data such as searching, sorting, insertion , manipulation and deletion etc.


It is recommended to stop the memory wastage as it grows on demand.



